Which of the following represents a correct configuration line for /etc/hosts?
A)  168.1.4 cwa.braingia.org cwa
B)  cwa.braingia.org cwa 168.1.4
C)  cwa.braingia.org 168.1.8 alias cwa
D)  alias cwa.braingia.org cwa 168.1.4
A
A. The correct format is IP address followed by canonical hostname and any aliases for thehost. You can use entries in /etc/hosts to override DNS lookups, which can be useful toprevent those names from resolving or to provide a different resolution.
